### English Title:
Egyptian Authorities Implement Strict Measures Against Food and Sweet Shops

### English Text Summary:
Egyptian authorities have taken stringent measures, including closures, against food and sweet shops to ensure food safety and consumer health. The campaign targeted several well-known establishments, including "Belben," which faced widespread backlash on social media after reports of food poisoning linked to its products. The National Food Safety Authority reported the presence of harmful bacteria and banned substances in various food items. Despite the company's claims that the closures were due to administrative issues and not health complaints, the situation escalated following complaints from citizens. The closures have affected over 25,000 workers, prompting discussions about the implications for the economy and food safety.

